Task 1: Data Redundancy Removal System 
Project Title
Cloud-Based Data Redundancy Removal System
Objective
The main objective of this project is to identify and remove duplicate records from a cloud database. The system validates new data before insertion and stores only unique records, thereby improving database efficiency, accuracy, and storage utilization.
Problem Statement
In cloud databases, duplicate records often occur due to:
Multiple user submissions
Data synchronization issues
Human entry mistakes
System integration errors
These duplicate records consume storage space, reduce performance, and create inconsistencies.
The proposed system automatically detects duplicates and prevents redundant data from being stored.
